cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI

This paper deals with load aware channel selection in 802.11 WLANs, which is a topic related to network protocols and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a learning-based approach using Gaussian Process Regressing, which falls under the category of machine learning and statistics. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also involves optimization of network performance, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms for optimization suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category.
